{"chunk_id": "177331a5-4c33-4951-9582-5f84c54cec1a", "source_database": "ICMR", "document_title": "ICMR_NIN_Dietary_Guidelines_Real.pdf", "publication_version": "Latest", "chunk_sequence_number": 169, "content_type": "Medical Guideline", "language": "English", "text": "whole nuts. /c63Moderate the use of animal foods containing high fat, SFA and cholesterol. /c63Limit the use of ghee, butter, especially vanaspati as a cooking oil. /c63Choose low- fat dairy foods in place of regular whole fat dairy foods. /c63Eat foods rich in alpha-linolenic (ALA) acid such as legumes, green leafy vegetables, fenugreek and mustard seeds. /c63Eat fish more frequently (at least 100-200g /week), prefer it to meat, poultry and limit/ avoid organ meats such as liver, kidney, brain etc. /c63Egg has several important nutrients but is high in cholesterol. Limit the consumption to 3 eggs/ week. However, egg white may be consumed in good amounts. /c63Minimize consumption of ready- to- eat fast foods, bakery foods and processed foods prepared in hydrogenated fat. /c63Use of", "embedding": [-0.004209098871797323, -0.019578982144594193, -0.039573993533849716, 0.03270304948091507, -0.0712571069598198, 0.042164772748947144, -0.07475466281175613, 0.06877006590366364, -0.05298623442649841, -0.08904805034399033, -0.03819587081670761, -0.04499533772468567, -0.15072347223758698, -0.11614847183227539, 0.04660963639616966, -0.048964254558086395, 0.11529170721769333, 0.029646843671798706, -0.06655515730381012, -0.04553240165114403, 0.019885867834091187, -0.07168766111135483, 0.019238680601119995, -0.017907116562128067, -0.024878110736608505, -0.04259572550654411, 0.06318822503089905, -0.07516836374998093, -0.0015036949189379811, -0.01702609658241272, 0.030008705332875252, -0.007086426019668579, 0.03111458569765091, -0.011695160530507565, -0.07529550790786743, -0.007728416007012129, -0.013907804153859615, -0.09454341977834702, -0.028627002611756325, -0.006828391458839178, 0.03973314166069031, 0.02357082441